import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Delay')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    avg_delay_by_distance_range = data.groupby('distance_range')['delay'].mean()
    avg_delay_by_distance_range.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Distance Range')
    plt.ylabel('Average Delay')
    plt.title('What is the average delay for each distance range?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
